div.div: Information occurs from relationships (intersections, interactions, collisions) between objects. When two objects collide, more information is generated than the information about the two object definitions, unless the relationship was predicted in their definitions (unlikely in a complex system).
The structure of position occurs from difference information

Information is generated by units of structural change (vectors) applied to existing objects to generate information about relationships. In the absence of objects, change vectors can align to generate attributes, which can accrete into objects.

These change vectors are either generated by object definitions, objects without mass, from other spaces (without time, integrated across time), or from the interface network, filtering in a way that produces vectors, which when combined with a precursor of information (some form of energy like potential), produce structure.
Information decays into limits/rules without change to sustain it or produce more.
Information is a high-energy state that stabilizes into its components when it's not needed (being used/observed or changed through interaction with other objects).
It also exists contextually unless it's observed/used/changed enough to become relevant to all space-times.

The decomposition of an information particle into its components involves storage of various metadata sets (system context, time, components needed to generate/derive/apply it, components needed to differentiate it, components needed to identify it), which decay into the ground state, a "stem cell" of information which has its original identity & context removed and could become any other bit of information (no system context except global system or a system capable of generating it like the interface network, and a set of components needed to build information molecules (concepts, relationships, intents filling a structure like position).

Each information molecule should in theory have a copy of the interface network or other system that can generate it - maybe in a network of sub-particles or interactions of core forces of the universe - unless it's not possible to reverse the process of crystallization into information.

Information interactions tend to have a compounding effect of creating distance in space-time: the more information you focus on, the farther into the past you get trapped in, and the harder it is to dig out without abstracting info manipulation methods (derivation, generation, etc). Space-times filled with information might as well not exist since they can't be changed (decay into a constant limit) - distributing abstraction methods could reverse enough information to create a variance cascade.

The information nearest to the big bang may be constants (pi, e & other universal constants), which implies different number types evolved with more information, allowing more possible structures for information to fill.
Â The energy operating between numerical objects follows physics rules.

The most common form of information may be an illusory boundary generated by its metadata, where the information seems measurable but it may actually be a gap between the generating metadata objects/attributes, and the information or the appearance of it (emergent attributes like a form) is what's left by the filter created by the gap, where information components pass through and interact to form that illusion. This is similar to viewing a set of filters from different angles - at various points around the filter set, you may see one type of light, at other points another type, and at other points only shadows - all considered information by the observer until they discover the filters.

Examine other base parameters for quantum scales: potential-based calculations, variance-based calculations, as opposed to evaluating change with respect to time (time attaches to or accretes from the most stable/efficient state).
